        .WidgetBoxContent
          %h3 Widget Icons

          .well Icons are created 32x32 pixels and sized down to 16x16 in the UI. This allows retina and higher-resolution mobile devices to look better.

          .warningwell I am unhappy with the alignment of text after these icons. Its inconsistent, sometimes high sometimes low. While none of them technically have text aligned with them in the app I would like to standardize this.
          %ul.captionbox
            %li
              %a.widgetbtn{"data-toggle" => "modal", :href => "#"}
                %i.gcmsicon-questionmark-grey
              Help button - should be on every widget and opens a modal with an edit (Crowdsourcing help)
            %li
              %a.widgetbtn{"data-toggle" => "modal", :href => "#"}
                %i.gcmsicon-edit-grey
              Edit button - This is only on widgets that do not have subareas with edit buttons. Possibly fully obsolete.
            %li
              %a.accordion-toggle.widgetbtn{"data-toggle" => "collapse", :href => "#"}
                %i.gcmsicon-enlarge-grey
              Show/Hide button - Shows widget content or hides the widget (animated to a single header bar unless content flagged to always show)
            %li
              %input.ui-corner-all.widgetsearch{:placeholder => "Search", :type => "text"}/
              While not an icon or button listed here for completion. Should always be present for filterable widgets.
          .infowell
            a.widgetbtn > i.gcmsicon-iconname
          .warningwell
            Because of non-opensource icons in twitter bootstrap, icons have had a few revisions to make them honest. However, this has left a lot of messy naming conventions in the css. All icons should be simplified to icon-name soon.
